{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Rom|11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","chapter":11,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":1,"text":"I ask, then, has God rejected his people? Absolutely not! For I too am an Israelite, a descendant of Abraham, from the tribe of Benjamin.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":2,"text":"God has not rejected his people whom he foreknew. Or don’t you know what the Scripture says in the passage about Elijah —how he pleads with God against Israel?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":3,"text":"Lord, they have killed your prophets and torn down your altars. I am the only one left, and they are trying to take my life!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":4,"text":"But what was God’s answer to him? I have left seven thousand for myself who have not bowed down to Baal.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":5,"text":"In the same way, then, there is also at the present time a remnant chosen by grace.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":6,"text":"Now if by grace, then it is not by works; otherwise grace ceases to be grace.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":7,"text":"What then? Israel did not find what it was looking for, but the elect did find it. The rest were hardened,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":8,"text":"as it is written,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":9,"text":"And David says,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":10,"text":"Let their eyes be darkened so that they cannot see,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":11,"text":"I ask, then, have they stumbled so as to fall? Absolutely not! On the contrary, by their transgression, salvation has come to the Gentiles to make Israel jealous.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":12,"text":"Now if their transgression brings riches for the world, and their failure riches for the Gentiles, how much more will their fullness bring!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":13,"text":"Now I am speaking to you Gentiles. Insofar as I am an apostle to the Gentiles, I magnify my ministry,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":14,"text":"if I might somehow make my own people jealous and save some of them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":15,"text":"For if their rejection brings reconciliation to the world, what will their acceptance mean but life from the dead?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":16,"text":"Now if the firstfruits are holy, so is the whole batch. And if the root is holy, so are the branches.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":17,"text":"Now if some of the branches were broken off, and you, though a wild olive branch, were grafted in among them and have come to share in the rich root of the cultivated olive tree,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":18,"text":"do not boast that you are better than those branches. But if you do boast —you do not sustain the root, but the root sustains you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":19,"text":"Then you will say, “Branches were broken off so that I might be grafted in.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":20,"text":"True enough; they were broken off because of unbelief, but you stand by faith. Do not be arrogant, but beware,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":21,"text":"because if God did not spare the natural branches, he will not spare you either.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":22,"text":"Therefore, consider God’s kindness and severity: severity toward those who have fallen but God’s kindness toward you —if you remain in his kindness. Otherwise you too will be cut off.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":23,"text":"And even they, if they do not remain in unbelief, will be grafted in, because God has the power to graft them in again.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":24,"text":"For if you were cut off from your native wild olive tree and against nature were grafted into a cultivated olive tree, how much more will these —the natural branches —be grafted into their own olive tree?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":25,"text":"I don’t want you to be ignorant of this mystery, brothers and sisters, so that you will not be conceited: A partial hardening has come upon Israel until the fullness of the Gentiles has come in.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":26,"text":"And in this way all Israel will be saved, as it is written,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":27,"text":"And this will be my covenant with them","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":28,"text":"Regarding the gospel, they are enemies for your advantage, but regarding election, they are loved because of the patriarchs,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":29,"text":"since God’s gracious gifts and calling are irrevocable.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":30,"text":"As you once disobeyed God but now have received mercy through their disobedience,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":31,"text":"so they too have now disobeyed, resulting in mercy to you, so that they also may now receive mercy.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":32,"text":"For God has imprisoned all in disobedience so that he may have mercy on all.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":33,"text":"Oh, the depth of the riches","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:34","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":34,"text":"For who has known the mind of the Lord?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:35","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":35,"text":"And who has ever given to God,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:36","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":11,"verse":36,"text":"For from him and through him","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","chapter":11,"paragraphStarts":[1,7,9,10,11,13,17,25,27,28,33,34,35,36],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Israel’s Rejection Not Total"},{"beforeVerse":11,"text":"Israel’s Rejection Not Final"},{"beforeVerse":33,"text":"A Hymn of Praise"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I ask, then, has God rejected his people? "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 12:22","book":"1Sa","chapter":12,"verse":22,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 33:24–26","book":"Jer","chapter":33,"verse":24,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" Absolutely not! "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 20:16","book":"Luk","chapter":20,"verse":16,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" For I too am an Israelite, a descendant of Abraham, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 11:22","book":"2Co","chapter":11,"verse":22,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Php 3:5","book":"Php","chapter":3,"verse":5,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" from the tribe of Benjamin. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 12:22","book":"1Sa","chapter":12,"verse":22},{"label":"Jr 33:24–26","book":"Jer","chapter":33,"verse":24},{"label":"Lk 20:16","book":"Luk","chapter":20,"verse":16},{"label":"2Co 11:22","book":"2Co","chapter":11,"verse":22},{"label":"Php 3:5","book":"Php","chapter":3,"verse":5}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"God has not rejected his people whom he foreknew. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 12:22","book":"1Sa","chapter":12,"verse":22,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 94:14","book":"Psa","chapter":94,"verse":14,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 8:29","book":"Rom","chapter":8,"verse":29,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 1:2","book":"1Pe","chapter":1,"verse":2,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" Or don’t you know "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 6:16","book":"Rom","chapter":6,"verse":16,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" what the Scripture says in the passage about Elijah —how he pleads with God against Israel? "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 12:22","book":"1Sa","chapter":12,"verse":22},{"label":"Ps 94:14","book":"Psa","chapter":94,"verse":14},{"label":"Rm 8:29","book":"Rom","chapter":8,"verse":29},{"label":"1Pt 1:2","book":"1Pe","chapter":1,"verse":2},{"label":"Rm 6:16","book":"Rom","chapter":6,"verse":16}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Lord, they have killed your prophets and torn down your altars. I am the only one left, and they are trying to take my life!"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 19:10","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 19:14","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":14,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 19:10","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":10,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 19:14","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":14,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Th 2:14","book":"1Th","chapter":2,"verse":14,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 19:10","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":10},{"label":"1Kg 19:14","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":14},{"label":"1Kg 19:10","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":10},{"label":"1Kg 19:14","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":14},{"label":"1Th 2:14","book":"1Th","chapter":2,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But what was God’s answer to him? I have left seven thousand for myself who have not bowed down to Baal."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 19:18","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":18,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 19:18","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":18,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 19:18","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":18},{"label":"1Kg 19:18","book":"1Ki","chapter":19,"verse":18}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"In the same way, then, there is also at the present time a remnant chosen by grace. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:27","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":27,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 19:4","book":"2Ki","chapter":19,"verse":4},{"label":"Rm 9:27","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":27}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now if by grace, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 4:4","book":"Rom","chapter":4,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" then it is not by works; otherwise grace ceases to be grace. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Other mss add But if of works it is no longer grace; otherwise work is no longer work."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 4:4","book":"Rom","chapter":4,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Other mss add But if of works it is no longer grace; otherwise work is no longer work."}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"What then? Israel did not find what it was looking for, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:31","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":31,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" but the elect did find it. The rest were hardened, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 6:52","book":"Mrk","chapter":6,"verse":52,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:18","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":18,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 11:25","book":"Rom","chapter":11,"verse":25,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 2:14","book":"2Co","chapter":2,"verse":14,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 9:31","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":31},{"label":"Mk 6:52","book":"Mrk","chapter":6,"verse":52},{"label":"Rm 9:18","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":18},{"label":"Rm 11:25","book":"Rom","chapter":11,"verse":25},{"label":"2Co 2:14","book":"2Co","chapter":2,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"as it is written,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And David says,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Let their eyes be darkened so that they cannot see,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I ask, then, have they stumbled so as to fall? Absolutely not! On the contrary, by their transgression, salvation has come to the Gentiles "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 28:28","book":"Act","chapter":28,"verse":28,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" to make Israel jealous. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ac 28:28","book":"Act","chapter":28,"verse":28}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now if their transgression brings riches for the world, and their failure riches for the Gentiles, how much more will their fullness bring! "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 11:25","book":"Rom","chapter":11,"verse":25,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 11:25","book":"Rom","chapter":11,"verse":25}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now I am speaking to you Gentiles. Insofar as I am an apostle to the Gentiles, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 9:15","book":"Act","chapter":9,"verse":15,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" I magnify my ministry, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ac 9:15","book":"Act","chapter":9,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"if I might somehow make my own people "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit flesh"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 29:14","book":"Gen","chapter":29,"verse":14,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 19:12","book":"2Sa","chapter":19,"verse":12,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:3","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":3,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" jealous and save some of them. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 1:21","book":"1Co","chapter":1,"verse":21,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 7:16","book":"1Co","chapter":7,"verse":16,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 9:22","book":"1Co","chapter":9,"verse":22,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Tm 1:15","book":"1Ti","chapter":1,"verse":15,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Tm 2:4","book":"1Ti","chapter":2,"verse":4,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Tm 1:9","book":"2Ti","chapter":1,"verse":9,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ti 3:5","book":"Tit","chapter":3,"verse":5,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 29:14","book":"Gen","chapter":29,"verse":14},{"label":"2Sm 19:12","book":"2Sa","chapter":19,"verse":12},{"label":"Rm 9:3","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":3},{"label":"1Co 1:21","book":"1Co","chapter":1,"verse":21},{"label":"1Co 7:16","book":"1Co","chapter":7,"verse":16},{"label":"1Co 9:22","book":"1Co","chapter":9,"verse":22},{"label":"1Tm 1:15","book":"1Ti","chapter":1,"verse":15},{"label":"1Tm 2:4","book":"1Ti","chapter":2,"verse":4},{"label":"2Tm 1:9","book":"2Ti","chapter":1,"verse":9},{"label":"Ti 3:5","book":"Tit","chapter":3,"verse":5}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit flesh"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For if their rejection brings reconciliation "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 5:11","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" to the world, what will their acceptance mean but life from the dead? "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 15:24","book":"Luk","chapter":15,"verse":24,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 15:32","book":"Luk","chapter":15,"verse":32,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 5:11","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":11},{"label":"Lk 15:24","book":"Luk","chapter":15,"verse":24},{"label":"Lk 15:32","book":"Luk","chapter":15,"verse":32}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now if the firstfruits are holy, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 15:17","book":"Num","chapter":15,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 10:37","book":"Neh","chapter":10,"verse":37,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 44:30","book":"Ezk","chapter":44,"verse":30,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" so is the whole batch. And if the root is holy, so are the branches."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Nm 15:17","book":"Num","chapter":15,"verse":17},{"label":"Neh 10:37","book":"Neh","chapter":10,"verse":37},{"label":"Ezk 44:30","book":"Ezk","chapter":44,"verse":30}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now if some of the branches were broken off, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 11:16","book":"Jer","chapter":11,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 15:2","book":"Jhn","chapter":15,"verse":2,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and you, though a wild olive branch, were grafted in among them "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Eph 2:12–13","book":"Eph","chapter":2,"verse":12,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" and have come to share in the rich root "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Other mss read the root and the richness"},{"kind":"text","text":" of the cultivated olive tree, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jr 11:16","book":"Jer","chapter":11,"verse":16},{"label":"Jn 15:2","book":"Jhn","chapter":15,"verse":2},{"label":"Eph 2:12–13","book":"Eph","chapter":2,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Other mss read the root and the richness"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"do not boast that you are better than those branches. But if you do boast —you do not sustain the root, but the root sustains you. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 4:22","book":"Jhn","chapter":4,"verse":22,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jn 4:22","book":"Jhn","chapter":4,"verse":22}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then you will say, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:19","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":19,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" “Branches were broken off so that I might be grafted in.” "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 9:19","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":19}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"True enough; they were broken off because of unbelief, but you stand by faith. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 5:2","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 10:12","book":"1Co","chapter":10,"verse":12,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 1:24","book":"2Co","chapter":1,"verse":24,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" Do not be arrogant, but beware, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Lit fear"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 12:16","book":"Rom","chapter":12,"verse":16,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Tm 6:17","book":"1Ti","chapter":6,"verse":17,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 1:17","book":"1Pe","chapter":1,"verse":17,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 5:2","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":2},{"label":"1Co 10:12","book":"1Co","chapter":10,"verse":12},{"label":"2Co 1:24","book":"2Co","chapter":1,"verse":24},{"label":"Rm 12:16","book":"Rom","chapter":12,"verse":16},{"label":"1Tm 6:17","book":"1Ti","chapter":6,"verse":17},{"label":"1Pt 1:17","book":"1Pe","chapter":1,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"Lit fear"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:11:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"because if God did not spare the natural branches, he will not spare you either. "}],"cro